Summary:

When Patrick O&#039;Brian passed away in 2000, he left behind three chapters of what was to be the 21st Aubrey-Maturin novel. The tale was to have followed Jack Aubrey in his new post, Rear Admiral of the Blue Squadron. Showing his storytelling gift until the end, O&#039;Brian did include a duel between Aubrey&#039;s trusted friend Stephen Maturin and an impertinent officer.

Although it remains unfinished, 21 gives us one final glance at the unparalleled genius of a master craftsman and the series The New York Times Book Review hailed as the best historical novels ever written.
